{"key":"post-16369317","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16369317</id>\n<content>Wheat and oat bran work fine.&amp;nbsp; Don't use whole wheat flour from the grocery store because it's usually just white flour with a tiny amount of whole wheat added to make it look brown.&amp;nbsp; They shouldn't even be able to call it whole wheat but they do.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As already said, simply buy a large bag of brown rice and grind it in a coffee grinder.&amp;nbsp; Health food stores sell rice bran in the refrigerated section and that's great.&amp;nbsp; Another option is to go to a feed store and get a large bag of rice bran for horses as shown below.&amp;nbsp; It's what I use for &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;brf tek&lt;/a&gt; and also as a supplement for sawdust substrates for our &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Mountain-Mushroom-Farm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;shiitake mushroom farm.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/09-15/920738766-Rice_Bran_for_Horses_001.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/09-15/920738766-thumb_Rice_Bran_for_Horses_001.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/09-15/920738861-Rice_Bran_for_Horses_002.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/09-15/920738861-thumb_Rice_Bran_for_Horses_002.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16369424</next>\n<prev>16369315</prev>\n<first>16367767</first>\n<last